29 May 2010 15:13






Thanks; it's my first effort, and I'm still working on getting the wording right.

I agree that the test logs need more, but I was trying to avoid falling into the 'It kills everyone' cliche, as well as putting too much into it at first. I have a number of ideas to explore with it, like the idea that the perception of the object is required, so that sedating a subject into unconsciousness (or having their eyes eaten/plucked/otherwise rendered inoperable) could terminate the effect.

As to the termination of D-Classes.. I think you may be right; I was trying to maintain the normal, rather callous feel about them (since they will be terminated at the end of the month, anyway), but perhaps the survivors should be help for additional testing.. I.e., test until destruction or their time is up.

Thanks for the feedback, tho.. I'm rather pleasantly surprised at the response, for a first effort :)







